      <title>The Caboose Pushes Rails Documentation</title>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;You&amp;#8217;ve probably noticed &lt;a href="http://slash7.com"&gt;many&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="http://robbyonrails.com"&gt;of&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="http://brainspl.at"&gt;the&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="http://www.jroller.com/page/obie"&gt;popular&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="http://www.nimblecode.com/"&gt;Rails&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="http://www.jvoorhis.com/"&gt;writers&lt;/a&gt; are &lt;a href="http://glu.ttono.us/"&gt;working&lt;/a&gt; on books. Since we&amp;#8217;re all off working on other sources of documentation we really haven&amp;#8217;t had time to work on the Rails API docs themselves. This is our attempt to push things in the right direction.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://habtm.com"&gt;Courtenay&lt;/a&gt; has &lt;a href="http://blog.caboo.se/articles/2006/08/04/the-caboose-rails-documentation-project"&gt;started up a paypal account&lt;/a&gt; for donations which would go to funding someone to give the API docs some sweet sweet lovin&amp;#8217;. We&amp;#8217;re shooting for 5000 USD. I&amp;#8217;ll be putting in $100 and some adsense revenue. Do your part. Help us get better docs.&lt;/p&gt;

